  <!--
  INSTRUCTIONS:

  Recommended deployment on Vercel:
  1. Add an Environment Variable in your Vercel Project: GROQ_API_KEY = <your-secret-key>
  2. Create a serverless function at /api/groq (example Node/Edge function code included below in comments).
  3. Deploy this index.html as your static site (e.g., put in the repo root or in 'public' and set as root).
  4. The frontend will call /api/groq; the serverless function will forward the request securely to https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions.

  Example Vercel serverless function (api/groq.js - Node):
  -----------------------------------------------------
  // api/groq.js
  export default async function handler(req, res) {
    if (req.method !== 'POST') {
      res.status(405).json({ error: 'Method not allowed' });
      return;
    }
    const GROQ_API_KEY = process.env.GROQ_API_KEY;
    if (!GROQ_API_KEY) return res.status(500).json({ error: 'GROQ_API_KEY not set' });

    try {
      const body = await req.json(); // pass-through object: model, messages, etc.
      const groqRes = await fetch('https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
          'Authorization': `Bearer ${GROQ_API_KEY}`
        },
        body: JSON.stringify(body)
      });
      const data = await groqRes.json();
      res.status(groqRes.status).json(data);
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(err);
      res.status(500).json({ error: 'Proxy error' });
    }
  }
  -----------------------------------------------------

  Note: For Vercel Edge Functions the code shape differs slightly. Use Node serverless if unsure.

  If you must call Groq directly from the browser (not recommended), set window.GROQ_API_KEY at build time (unsafe).
  -->

  <style>
